epsg:alias.epsg:remarks: This EuroGeographics identifier is for a CRS similar to this but with CS axes in order north, east.

ProjectedCRS.name: OSGB 1936 / British National Grid
ProjectedCRS.scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping and engineering survey.

GeodeticDatum.name: OSGB 1936
GeodeticDatum.remarks: The average accuracy of OSTN02 compared to the old triangulation network (down to 3rd order) is 0.1m.
GeodeticDatum.anchorDefinition: From April 2002 the datum is defined through the application of the OSTN02 transformation (tfm code 1039) to ETRS89. Prior to 2002, fundamental point: Herstmonceux, Latitude: 50°51'55.271"N, longitude: 0°20'45.882"E (of Greenwich).

epsg:AreaOfUse.name: UK - Great Britain; Isle of Man

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: United Kingdom (UK) - Great Britain - England and Wales onshore, Scotland onshore and Western Isles nearshore; Isle of Man onshore.

Ellipsoid.name: Airy 1830
Ellipsoid.remarks: Original definition is a=20923713, b=20853810 feet of 1796. 1/f is given to 7 decimal places. For the 1936 retriangulation OSGB defines the relationship of 10 feet of 1796 to the International metre through ([10^0.48401603]/10) exactly = 0.3048007491...

EllipsoidalCS.name: Ellipsoidal 2D CS. Axes: latitude, longitude. Orientations: north, east. UoM: degree
EllipsoidalCS.remarks: Coordinates referenced to this CS are in degrees. Any degree representation (e.g. DMSH, decimal, etc.) may be used but that used must be declared for the user by the supplier of data. Used in geographic 2D coordinate reference systems.

epsg:CommonMetaData.epsg:informationSource: ISO 19111 "Geographical information - Spatial referencing by coordinates".

epsg:AxisName.description: Height influenced by the Earth's gravity field. In particular, orthometric height or normal height which are both approximations of the distance of a point above sea level. Positive upwards.
epsg:AxisName.name: Gravity-related height
epsg:AxisName.remarks: Used in a 1D vertical coordinate system.

epsg:AxisName.description: Angle from the equatorial plane to the perpendicular to the ellipsoid through a given point, northwards usually treated as positive.
epsg:AxisName.name: Geodetic latitude
epsg:AxisName.remarks: Used in geographic 2D and geographic 3D coordinate reference systems.

epsg:AxisName.description: Angle from the prime meridian plane to the meridian plane passing through the given point, eastwards usually treated as positive.
epsg:AxisName.name: Geodetic longitude
epsg:AxisName.remarks: Used in geographic 2D and geographic 3D coordinate reference systems.

epsg:AxisName.description: East pointing axis used in 2D projected coordinate systems.
epsg:AxisName.name: Easting

epsg:AxisName.description: North pointing axis used in 2D projected coordinate systems.
epsg:AxisName.name: Northing

CartesianCS.name: Cartesian 2D CS. Axes: easting, northing (E,N). Orientations: east, north. UoM: m.
CartesianCS.remarks: Used in projected and engineering coordinate reference systems.

VerticalCRS.name: EGM2008 geoid height
VerticalCRS.remarks: Height surface resulting from the application of the EGM2008 geoid model to the WGS 84 ellipsoid. Replaces EGM96 geoid (CRS code 5773).

VerticalCS.name: Vertical CS. Axis: height (H). Orientation: up. UoM: m.
VerticalCS.remarks: Used in vertical coordinate reference systems.

CartesianCS.name: Cartesian 2D CS. Axes: 1st local axis, 2nd local axis (X,Y). Orientations: north, west. UoM: m.
CartesianCS.remarks: Used in engineering coordinate reference systems.

epsg:AxisName.description: First axis of any local coordinate system.
epsg:AxisName.name: First local axis
epsg:AxisName.remarks: First and second local coordinate axes are assumed to be horizontal and may be supplemented by 'local height' or 'local depth' to form a local 3D coordinate system.

epsg:AxisName.description: Second axis of any local coordinate system.
epsg:AxisName.name: Second local axis

SphericalCS.name: Spherical 3D CS. Axes: latitude, longitude, radius. Orientations: north, east, up. UoM: degrees, degrees, metres.
SphericalCS.remarks: Used in geocentric 3D coordinate reference systems.

epsg:AxisName.description: Angle from the equatorial plane to the geocentric point vector, northwards usually treated as positive.
epsg:AxisName.name: Spherical latitude

epsg:AxisName.description: Angle from the prime meridian plane to the meridian plane passing through a point, eastwards usually treated as positive.
epsg:AxisName.name: Spherical longitude

epsg:AxisName.description: The distance from the (geocentric) coordinate system origin to a point. The third axis of a spherical coordinate system.
epsg:AxisName.name: Geocentric radius
epsg:AxisName.remarks: Used to avoid the singularity when the two angles in a 3D polar coordinate system lie in the same plane.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Europe - onshore - Andorra; Austria; Belgium; Bosnia and Herzegovina; Bulgaria; Croatia; Czech Republic; Denmark; Estonia; Finland; France - mainland; Germany; Hungary; Italy - mainland and Sicily; Latvia; Liechtenstein; Lithuania; Luxembourg; Netherlands; Norway; Poland; Portugal; Romania; San Marino; Slovakia; Slovenia; Spain - mainland; Sweden; Switzerland; United Kingdom (UK) - Great Britain mainland; Vatican City State.

epsg:CommonMetaData.epsg:informationSource: EPSG. See 3D CRS for original information source.

GeodeticCRS.name: ETRS89
GeodeticCRS.remarks: The distinction in usage between ETRF89 and ETRS89 is confused: although in principle conceptually different in practice both are used as synonyms.

VerticalCRS.name: EVRF2007 height
VerticalCRS.remarks: Placeholder to reserve CRS code ahead of full availability of datum origin description. Replaces EVRF2000 height (CRS code 5730).
VerticalCRS.scope: Geodetic survey, topographic mapping, engineering survey.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Europe - onshore and offshore: Albania; Andorra; Austria; Belgium; Bosnia and Herzegovina; Bulgaria; Croatia; Cyprus; Czech Republic; Denmark; Estonia; Faroe Islands; Finland; France; Germany; Gibraltar; Greece; Hungary; Ireland; Italy; Latvia; Liechtenstein; Lithuania; Luxembourg; Macedonia; Malta; Monaco; Montenegro; Netherlands; Norway including Svalbard and Jan Mayen; Poland; Portugal; Romania; San Marino; Serbia; Slovakia; Slovenia; Spain; Sweden; Switzerland; United Kingdom (UK) including Channel Islands and Isle of Man; Vatican City State.

GeodeticDatum.name: European Terrestrial Reference System 1989
GeodeticDatum.remarks: The distinction in usage between ETRF89 and ETRS89 is confused: although in principle conceptually different in practice both are used for the realisation.
GeodeticDatum.anchorDefinition: Fixed to the stable part of the Eurasian continental plate and consistent with ITRS at the epoch 1989.0.

epsg:alias.epsg:remarks: Adopted by IUGG 1979 Canberra as the Geodetic Reference Spheroid of 1980 (GRS 1980).

epsg:CommonMetaData.epsg:informationSource: "Geodetic Reference System 1980" by H. Moritz; Bulletin Geodesique

Ellipsoid.name: GRS 1980
Ellipsoid.remarks: Adopted by IUGG 1979 Canberra. Inverse flattening is derived from geocentric gravitational constant GM = 3986005e8 m*m*m/s/s; dynamic form factor J2 = 108263e8 and Earth's angular velocity = 7292115e-11 rad/s.

epsg:CommonMetaData.epsg:informationSource: European veritical data centre at Bundesamt für Kartographie und Geodäsie (BKG), Leipzig branch. http://crs.bkg.bund.de/evrs/

VerticalDatum.name: European Vertical Reference Frame 2007
VerticalDatum.remarks: Realised by geopotential numbers and Normal heights of the United European Levelling Network. Replaces EVRF2000 (datum code 5129).
